		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message30502015">Or JoJo. The over the top style and creativity really gets people fired up. Though JoJo does have highly creative battles. The battle between JoJo and Whamuuuuuuuuu was overflowing with creative juices. That and the style build on each other to make a full package. <br />
<br />
A video game that my brother and I talk about that is all style and no substance is No More Heroes. The characters are shallow, the world is shallow, and the the side missions are shallow. What it has going for it is the eccentric and flashy bosses and the cheesy but fun dialogue. The rest is so bland that it doesn't support the style. I do think that unless you're looking at a painting you need something else there to back it up or support the style. Sure, a work can swing more in favor of style but there needs to be a backbone to the piece.<br />
<br />
Baccano! had likable characters with different ideals who clashed. A lot of the entrainment was from seeing these eccentric personalities challenge each other in a stylized fashion. Also, the music, the unique storytelling, and refreshing setting all built into the enjoyment of the show. There's more than just style here.<br />
<br />
A cake can look pretty but it also has to taste good.</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
