		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message30504641">Sure. Why not? I'm not a fan of this dichotomy of style and substance because it's written under such terrible pretenses: that somehow story progression, character development, scripting,... is separate from presentation—that style must only be added fluff to appease the viewer while he/she examines the """""real"""" component of the work.<br />
<br />
I would even take the opposite view that "substance" requires "style". If the presentation isn't integrated into the core development of the work, then there's little reason for it to exist in the first place. The work may as well be a book, if that and not some chronicle in encyclopedic format.<br />
<br />
I can imagine where the phrase comes from. A work may in fact be "style over substance" if its style exists in a vacuum and without a purpose. However, I think this should be taken with a grain of salt, because assuming that the claim is even true, it negatively connotes that the work aimed (and failed) to have substance to begin with. Kick-Heart is "style over substance" because like most other animated shorts, it's made to entertain and to flaunt only its experimental visuals; Jojo, Redline, Panty and Stocking, and Kill la Kill are "style over substance" because their presentation with bombastic music, creative animation, and voluptuous ladies have little purpose other than to please the viewer. "Style over substance" is not a valid criticism for these(!).<br />
<br />
Here's a laundry list of examples/not examples: (I'm really sorry for these lists but I'm hoping people better get how I view the phrase by the common ideas in the works I'm grouping together. nevermind if you disagree with one or two so long as you get the big picture)<div class="spoiler"><input type="button" class="button" onClick="this.nextSibling.nextSibling.style.display='block';this.style.display='none';" value="Show spoiler"> <span class="spoiler_content" style="display:none"><input type="button" class="button" onClick="this.parentNode.style.display='none';this.parentNode.parentNode.childNodes[0].style.display='block';" value="Hide spoiler"><br>Where style is substance:<br />
Akira<br />
Arakawa<br />
Aria<br />
DRRR<br />
FLCL<br />
Gunbuster<br />
Haibane Renmei<br />
Jinrui<br />
Kaiba<br />
Katanagatari<br />
Kino no Tabi<br />
all Anno/Kon/Oshii/Watanabe/Ikuhara works<br />
Monogatari<br />
Mononoke<br />
NHK<br />
Ping Pong<br />
Serial Experiments Lain<br />
SZS<br />
Tatami<br />
Tsumiki no Ie<br />
<br />
Where "style over substance" is a valid criticism:<br />
Black Rock Shooter<br />
Code Geass<br />
Death Note<br />
Fate/Zero<br />
Higashi no Eden<br />
Hoshi no Koe<br />
Mariaholic<br />
Sasami-san<br />
Tekkon Kinkreet<!--spoiler--></span></div></div><div style="margin-top: 8px;"><em>Modified by nil-, 05-04-14, 1:21 PM</em></div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><div style="text-align: center;"><!--link--><a href="http://myanimelist.net/clubs.php?cid=40791">QD</a><!--center--></div></div></td>
