Great video. I was lost in the mood. I still think there's something there, something to be talked about from that piece. Even without words, music is a language that we can take something from, and like any language we can interpret it. It makes us feel a certain way. Morimoto creates his music which gets the listener to get lost in his mood. We can discuss the piece for it's animation quality and trance-like depictions of violence shown. "Why was this made?" and "What does it mean?" "How does it make me feel" we can ask.</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
